posts.raw_content:
Hi all, 

I'm humbly asking for prayers for good results from this. I had a mammogram a few weeks ago that showed multiple suspicious masses in both breasts and a "pathologic axillary lymph node". Today I had biopsies and a total of 6 separate tissue samples were taken. 

The radiologist's report regarding the diagnostic ultrasound I had after the mammo rated these results as BIRAD 5, meaning >95% likelihood of malignancy. 

I've already gone through treatment for thyroid cancer in the last 3 years. It was rough. I'm single, I do not have the support system needed for cancer treatment nor do I wish to go through any cancer treatment beyond removing a large mass that is causing pain. 

I'm ok with whatever the results are. I'm aging, something is going to take me out at some point. I would really like to not spend my last few years of life living with cancer though, so prayers please. 

Thanks friends
